<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="18" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="18.[93,620,211,1238]" pageId="18" pageNumber="18">
COMMENTS: The AMNH number of the 
<typeStatus box="[93,195,479,501]" pageId="18" pageNumber="18">holotype</typeStatus>
was given in the original description. 
<typeStatus box="[164,272,509,530]" pageId="18" pageNumber="18">Paratype</typeStatus>
: 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[293,482,508,529]" pageId="18" pageNumber="18">AMNH 658278</emphasis>
, immature male, collected in the mountains of Goodenough Island, by A.S. Meek, in 1913. 
<bibRefCitation author="Dickinson, E. C." box="[93,360,596,619]" pageId="18" pageNumber="18" refId="ref131767" refString="Dickinson, E. C. (editor). 2003. The Howard &amp; Moore complete checklist of the birds of the world. 3 rd ed. London: Christopher Helm, 1039 pp." type="book" year="2003">Dickinson (2003: 476)</bibRefCitation>
synonymized 
<emphasis box="[539,619,597,618]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="18">remota</emphasis>
with 
<emphasis box="[159,240,625,648]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="18">bartoni</emphasis>
of southeastern New 
<collectingCountry box="[526,614,626,648]" name="Guinea-Bissau" pageId="18" pageNumber="18">Guinea</collectingCountry>
, probably based on 
<bibRefCitation author="Galbraith, I. C. J." box="[344,615,655,677]" pageId="18" pageNumber="18" pagination="133 - 222" refId="ref132624" refString="Galbraith, I. C. J. 1956. Variation, relationships and evolution in the Pachycephala pectoralis superspecies (Aves, Muscicapidae). Bulletin of the British Museum (Natural History) Zoology 4: 133 - 222, map." type="journal article" year="1956">Galbraith (1956: 196)</bibRefCitation>
. However, Galbraith would not have seen the description of 
<emphasis box="[260,340,715,736]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="18">remota</emphasis>
, also published in 1956. This is undoubtedly an uncommon bird of the highest mountain on Goodenough. The single adult was collected at 
<quantity box="[464,560,803,825]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6" pageId="18" pageNumber="18" unit="m" value="1600.0">1600 m</quantity>
. We (
<bibRefCitation author="LeCroy, M. &amp; W. S. Peckover" box="[101,474,832,855]" pageId="18" pageNumber="18" pagination="41 - 44" refId="ref138237" refString="LeCroy, M., and W. S. Peckover. 2000. Birds observed on Goodenough and Wagifa islands, Milne Bay Province. Muruk 8: 41 - 44." type="journal article" year="2000">LeCroy and Peckover, 2000: 42</bibRefCitation>
) saw it only once when we were camped at 
<quantity box="[491,583,862,884]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.06" pageId="18" pageNumber="18" unit="m" value="1060.0">1060 m</quantity>
in 
<date box="[93,247,891,913]" pageId="18" pageNumber="18" value="1988-08">August 1988</date>
. Given the considerably larger size of the two Goodenough specimens compared to specimens of 
<emphasis box="[459,540,950,973]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="18">bartoni</emphasis>
from southeastern New 
<collectingCountry box="[324,410,980,1002]" name="Guinea-Bissau" pageId="18" pageNumber="18">Guinea</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Mayr, E. &amp; H. M. van Deusen" pageId="18" pageNumber="18" pagination="1 - 8" refId="ref140500" refString="Mayr, E., and H. M. van Deusen. 1956. Results of the Archbold Expeditions. No. 74. The birds of Goodenough Island, Papua. American Museum Novitates 1792: 1 - 8." type="journal article" year="1956">
Mayr and 
<taxonomicName authority="Deusen" authorityName="Deusen" class="Aves" family="Melanocharitidae" genus="Melanocharis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="18" pageNumber="162" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="van">Van Deusen</taxonomicName>
, 1956: 4
</bibRefCitation>
, and substantiated by my measurements), I believe the subspecies should be recognized, 
<emphasis box="[403,476,1069,1090]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="18">contra</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Dickinson, E. C." pageId="18" pageNumber="18" refId="ref131767" refString="Dickinson, E. C. (editor). 2003. The Howard &amp; Moore complete checklist of the birds of the world. 3 rd ed. London: Christopher Helm, 1039 pp." type="book" year="2003">Dickinson (2003: 476)</bibRefCitation>
. Further collecting is encouraged.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[93,620,211,1238]" pageId="18" pageNumber="18">
Rothschild and Hartert (1914a) reported on Meek’s collection from Goodenough Island. 
<collectingRegion box="[185,224,1187,1208]" country="South Sudan" name="Lakes" pageId="18" pageNumber="18">See</collectingRegion>
<bibRefCitation author="Brass, L. J." box="[237,387,1187,1209]" pageId="18" pageNumber="18" pagination="77 - 152" refId="ref129960" refString="Brass, L. J. 1956. Results of the Archbold Expeditions. No. 75. Summary of the Fourth Archbold Expedition to New Guinea (1953). Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History 111 (2): 77 - 152, 12 pls." type="book chapter" year="1956">Brass (1956)</bibRefCitation>
for a summary of the Fourth Archbold Expedition.
</paragraph>
